The prediction performance of the network model was examined by comparing the values obtained from the prediction of the developed ANN models with the target values. When the graphs are examined, the predicted values for each data point are in good agreement with the target values (Fig. 8
                        ). This fit illustrates that the designed ANN model can predict each output parameter with high accuracy. The values of margin of deviation calculated for each output value were generally low (Fig. 9
                        ). Similarly, the differences between the target values and the values generated by the ANN model are represented in Fig. 10
                        . The fact that MoD and difference values are very low proves that the designed ANN model can make predictions with high accuracy, confidence, stability, and minimal variability or very low errors in the data points under consideration (Çolak et al., 2023). Fig. 11
                         shows the target data on the x-axis and on the y-axis represents the values obtained from the ANN model. Examination of the data points reveals that they are generally on the zero-error line. For the developed ANN model, the calculated MSE and R2 value was 1.99E-03 and 0.99939 respectively. The present research finding has revealed that the designed ANN model can predict 10 separate output parameters with very high accuracy and very minimal error.
